# Weather API (RLUSD variant) -- example env.
# Copy to .env and fill in. Only PAYER_SEED is REQUIRED; the rest has
# sensible testnet defaults.
#
# WARNING: never commit .env. Never put real seeds in .env in production.

# ---- Payer wallet (REQUIRED) ----------------------------------------------
# Seed (sEd...) of a testnet wallet that *already* holds testnet RLUSD.
# Ripple does NOT expose a programmatic faucet for RLUSD, so this demo
# cannot mint it for you. Two ways to get a pre-funded seed:
#   1. https://tryrlusd.com -- official testnet RLUSD distributor (manual)
#   2. Open a trustline to `rQhWct2fv4Vc4KRjRgMrxa8xPN9Zx9iLKV` from any
#      testnet account you control, then request RLUSD from the faucet
#      above. The `setup-trustline.ts` script in this folder does this
#      for you in one command.
# The wallet must also hold a small XRP balance (~10 XRP) for the
# trustline reserve and per-tx fees.
PAYER_SEED=sEd...

# ---- Recipient wallet (optional) -------------------------------------------
# Server-side wallet that collects per-call RLUSD revenue. If unset, the
# server auto-funds a fresh ephemeral wallet via the XRPL testnet faucet
# at boot and opens its own trustline to the RLUSD issuer. Set this if
# you want a persistent recipient address across restarts.
# RECIPIENT_SEED=sEd...
